The bail decision for self-proclaimed Shepherd Bushiri and his wife Mary has been postponed until Wednesday. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The bail decision for self-proclaimed Shepherd Bushiri, his wife Mary, and three others has been postponed until Wednesday. The accused face charges of fraud, theft, and money laundering to the value of over R100-million. READ: Bushiri couple return to court for bail hearing The state says Bushiri and his wife are flight risks. The couple has been in custody for almost two weeks. Bushiri's supporters were outside the Pretoria Magistrate's court to show their support. Watch the video above for more details from the court